title: Comic Book Review: Captain Marvel #1
body:
Comic Book Review: Captain Marvel #1

No better book to pick up this year for Captain Marvel fans. With the world premiere of the movie right around the corner, this is probably one of the most important book debuts for the captain. After getting to know Carol Danvers more intimately after her latest mini story, I felt anxious to see what would come next when she goes back to work. When they hype this up as an oversized issue that…

summary: Nick Fury Will Lose His Eye in Captain Marvel
title: Nick Fury Will Lose His Eye in Captain Marvel
body:
Nick Fury Will Lose His Eye in #CaptainMarvel

One of the fan debates surrounding Captain Marvel when it was revealed that Nick Fury would appear in the movie has been whether or not the movie will reveal how he loses his eye. Most fans are convinced it’ll happen in the movie, while there are others who doubt that. Now we have confirmation that it does happen, although we’ll have to wait for the movie to see the details.

Samuel L. Jackson…

Your favorite creators provide commentaries on their latest issues. Right now you can get Kelly Thompson on Captain Marvel #1, Sina Grace on Iceman #5 and colorist Marissa Louise and me on Hex Wives #3, all of which are in stores today!

summary: not that it matters, but is Carol Danvers going to be in her 40s or 50s during Endgame? Bc her movie takes place in the 80s....
body:
not that it matters, but is Carol Danvers going to be in her 40s or 50s during Endgame? Bc her movie takes place in the 80s.

They’ll probably say she was in very convenient suspended animation, or that her powers give her longevity.

summary: Do you know how tiring it is telling people that your best friend lives in space? They give you that look...that look people...
body:
Do you know how tiring it is telling people that your best friend lives in space? They give you that look…that look people give 13-year-old boys who say they have a supermodel girlfriend who lives in Canada.

I get to be the canadian supermodel in this analogy?

You do.

summary:
Captain Marvel (2019) #1
I'd like to thank God, Jesus and the five people at Marvel who did not let Civil War 2 sink this...
body:
Captain Marvel (2019) #1

I’d like to thank God, Jesus and the five people at Marvel who did not let Civil War 2 sink this beautiful, god-tier ship. 💕 There’s another panel before the last where they talk about the aftermath of Civil War 2 but Tumblr keeps flagging that screenshot — it’s frustrating because they talk about Rhodey’s PTSD but also Carol’s trauma and it’s such a good panel.
